  "about": {
    "windowTitle": "01_about",
    "meta": "markdown · sh",
    "command": "cat about.md",
    "sections": [
      {
        "title": "main",
        "items": [
          "Frontend: layout and interfaces — landing pages, SPAs, dashboards and admin panels. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, TypeScript, React, Next.js, responsive UI and motion.",
          "Backend: REST/GraphQL APIs, auth, roles, databases, cache and background jobs. Node.js, Python, Go, PHP — stack chosen per project.",
          "Integrations: payments, email, webhooks, CRM and third-party APIs when services need to talk to each other.",
          "AI for automation: chatbots, classification, text generation — only when it saves time or cost vs doing it manually."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "also",
        "items": [
          "Desktop: Tauri, Electron — when you need an app outside the browser on Windows, macOS or Linux.",
          "Systems & native: Rust, C++, C# — when performance or low-level work matters.",
          "Legacy & niche: 1C, Lua — when it is already in the project or solves a specific task fast."
        ]
      },
      {
        "title": "approach",
        "items": [
          "Understand the task and MVP first, then grow — no bloat or checkbox features.",
          "Document key decisions, keep code readable, deliver something maintainable.",
          "Reach out via Contact — we will discuss the task, timeline and find a solution."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
